<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP19_Balance" s="458007">
  <T n="category">443724<!--tutorial_Category_Fairies--></T>
  <T n="name">0x93AB0540<!--Balance & Imbalance--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_Balance_Slide1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:250b12eeaf0f2da0</T>
      <T n="text">0xF8EA8590<!--Balance represents the overall state of Sims aged Teen and older, based on their long-term mood. It influences most aspects of a Sim's life—such as Moodlets, Need Decay, Skill Building, Luck, and even contracting Ailments.\n\nOver time, Sims in persistent bad moods will go from <font color="#199C2C"><b>Balanced</b></font>, to <font color="#199C2C"><b>Imbalanced</b></font>, then <font color="#199C2C"><b>Very Imbalanced</b></font>. Some life events, like the loss of a loved one or birth of a child, also have immediate impact on Balance.\n\nYou can opt all Sims out of Balance at any time. In the Main Menu, select <font color="#199C2C"><b>Game Options > Pack Settings</b></font> and find the toggle for <font color="#199C2C"><b>Enable Balance & Imbalance</b></font>.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_Balance_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:250b12eeaf0f2da3</T>
      <T n="text">0x742A9CF9<!--<font color="#199C2C"><b>Balanced</b></font>\nBalance is the typical state a Sim is in. Staying in a positive mood most of the time and caring for Needs will help a Sim stay in Balance. Persistent negative moods will reduce a Sim's Balance over time until they become Imbalanced.\n\n<font color="#199C2C"><b>Imbalanced</b></font>\nBeing Imbalanced means that a Sim's Needs will require more attention and care. They might need to eat more frequently, or care for their Hygiene more often. Sims may also experience slower Skill building, or worse Luck!\n\n<font color="#199C2C"><b>Very Imbalanced</b></font>\nIn addition to the effects above, Sims who are Very Imbalanced will suffer from <font color="#199C2C"><b>Ailments</b></font> until they are able to get back towards Balance. When returning to Balanced, <font color="#199C2C"><b>Ailments</b></font> may stick around but don't worry—it's temporary.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_Balance_Slide3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:250b12eeaf0f2da2</T>
      <T n="text">0x2F76A9FE<!--Beyond maintaining positive moods over time, there are a variety of ways for Sims to recover and remain Balanced:\n\n• <font color="#199C2C"><b>Visit a Naturopath</b></font> via the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Phone</b></font> under Home\n• <font color="#199C2C"><b>Meditating in Nature</b></font> with a high level of <font color="#199C2C"><b>Natural Living Skill</b></font>\n• Crafting and drinking certain <font color="#199C2C"><b>Apothecary Elixirs</b></font>\n• Maintaining <font color="#199C2C"><b>Live Houseplants</b></font>\n• Curing any existing <font color="#199C2C"><b>Ailments</b></font>--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
